\title{Period of a State in Markov Chain}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
  For a Markov chain with transition matrix #{Q}, the \strong{period} of a state #{i} is the greatest common divisor of all integers #{n} such that the #{(i, i)} entry of #{Q^n} is positive.

  ##{
    d(i) = \gcd \{ n \in \mathbb{N} \mid (Q^n)_{i, i} > 0 \}
  }
}

\p{
  If #{d(i) = 1}, then the state #{i} is \strong{aperiodic}, otherwise it is \strong{periodic}.
}
